20/12/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The new BiH government council for co-operation on police issues held its first session in Sarajevo Monday (19 December). 
BiH Security Minister Barisa Colak, who is council chairman, said the panel would establish an efficient mechanism for collaboration among the police agencies in BiH and make decisions about police reform.
In other news Monday, the European Commission Delegation in BiH and EUFOR sealed ten contracts totaling 1m euros and aimed at supporting sustainable return projects. 
The agreements envision the rebuilding and modernisation of infrastructure, health facilities, schools and kindergartens in seven municipalities, including Srebrenica and Visegrad. 
(BiH Council of Ministers Web site, Fena, PBS BiH - 19/12/05)
